Regression test for the Stage 4.2 loud-failure guard on surviving
SAWCore Nat#rec / Pos#rec.

Background. The Lean backend maps SAW's binary-positive `Nat` (Zero
| NatPos Pos) to Lean's unary `Nat` (zero | succ Nat) for clean
output. Their recursors have different case shapes — emitting
`@Nat.rec` against SAW-ordered branches would silently change
meaning. The translator therefore refuses with a clear
`UnsoundRecursor` TranslationError if a Nat#rec or Pos#rec ever
makes it past `scNormalize` to the emission stage.

This test constructs such a term explicitly via `parse_core` and
asserts that SAW exits with an error containing the expected
diagnostic. Pinned in `nat_rec.log.good`. If the guard ever
silently succeeds (and emits a broken Lean file), this test fails
loudly.
